The paper discusses a computational method for uncertainty quantification in nano-scale devices and circuits, which involves simulating integrated circuits and MEMS at a small number of quadrature samples and estimating a huge number of solution samples via a low-rank and tensor-recovery method. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including numerical analysis (cs.NA), machine learning (cs.MS), control systems (cs.SY), electronic devices and circuits (cs.ET), and electromagnetics (cs.EM). Among these, cs.NA and cs.MS seem to be the most likely categories, as the paper focuses on developing a computational method for solving high-dimensional uncertainty quantification problems, which involves numerical simulations and tensor recovery.
